		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						) Sublimanda bona omnia: aut
						circumvenient Mala.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>All good things must be raised: or bad things encircle them.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						<!-- Continued from facing page, tail, Ha2.189v -->
						= Magnoru[m] negociatoru[m] axioma chrematisticum.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>The chrematistic axiom of the greatest trades.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Corpus ante omnia debet respondere Animo: et quo&agrave;d fieri potest, etiam status
						Oeconomicus. Qualis est animus, tale esse debet illius instrumentum.
						Militaris animi Corpus debet esse solidum, robustum, velox; laboris
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						patientiss[im]u[m] ad omnia dexterrimum.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>Before all, the body ought to respond to the mind: and that can be done, even the economic condition. <!--JG: Unsure abt 'status economicus'-->
			As the mind is, so it ought to be instrument of the body. 
				The body of the military mind ought to be solid, robust, and quick; and most skillfully capable for everything of work.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Pragmatici Animi decet Corpus esse sanum, viuidum, agile:  assidua[e]
							<!-- Continues onto facing page, right margin, Ha2.189v -->
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>It is fitting that the body of a pragmatic mind is healty, lively, and agile:</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
